summary:
During my bachelor's at Örebro University I discovered my passion for working with food. Studying Arts and Meal Science peaked my interest for food and the industry. I decided to do my internship at one of Sweden's biggest commercial kitchen wholesale company, Menigo Foodservice. Working at the product and quality department introduced me the broadness and complexity of the industry. Working at Menigo thought me the importance of clear communication, structure and ability to be creative. After my internship I was offered to join the department during my summer leave.

Shortly after I graduated I decided to leave my hometown to close a very long and important chapter. I moved to the Netherlands to start my new chapter of life with a lot of strong and positive energy. 

Today I work as a Catalog Associate SE for Amazon. Working at Amazon has made my skills in analytical thinking excel. I have also found an interest for working with data and combining analytical issues with creativity.
